---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Who writes Signal and Noise, and why."
	pubDate={new Date('August 08 2021')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Signal &amp; Noise is a music blog built on the conviction that good writing about music should
		be honest, specific, and occasionally opinionated in ways that make people argue. Every genre
		deserves serious attention. Popularity is not a credential, and obscurity is not a virtue.
	</p>

	<p>
		The person behind it has been listening obsessively for a long time. The deep end of the pool
		has always been alternative and goth (the Cure, Bauhaus, Cocteau Twins, the whole sprawling
		post-punk family tree), but the playlist extends well beyond that. Jazz, ambient, hip hop, soul,
		country, metal, noise, classical. If it has something to say, it gets a listen.
	</p>

	<p>
		The goal here is not to tell you what to like. It is to write about music in a way that makes
		you want to go find it yourself. Sometimes that means a proper review. Sometimes it is a deep
		dive into an album that came out thirty years ago and still sounds like nothing else. Sometimes
		it is just a few hundred words about why a particular song gets stuck in your head at 2am.
	</p>

	<p>
		No algorithms, no streams, no sponsored content. Just records and the people who care about them.
	</p>
</Layout>
